wikipedia_page.main: Dawn Holden (born 1 September 1980) is an English former cricketer who played as a slow left-arm orthodox bowler and right-handed batter. She played 3 Test matches and 32 One Day Internationals for England between 1999 and 2004. She played domestic cricket for East Midlands, Nottinghamshire, Western Australia and Queensland.
